Interstitial cystitis and endometriosis in a 12-year-old girl. Interstitial cystitis (IC) is a common cause of pelvic pain in the general female population and is thought to be understated in young female patients.A 12-year-old girl with IC and endometriosis.A single case report.It is important to screen for IC in young patients with endometriosis and vice versa.